From our farm, to your plate"][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_row_inner text_style="light" background_color="#614b3d"][vc_column_inner padding_size="no-padding"][wyde_info_box icon_set="farming" icon_farming="fm-cafe-sign" icon_size="large" color="#fee299" title="Cafe Opening Hours"]Tuesday - Friday: 11.00am - 4.00pm Saturday - Sunday: 9.00am - 6.00pm Lunch is served from 11.30pm - 2.30pm Coffee, teas, cold drinks and cakes in the mornings and afternoons. - Closed Mondays -[/wyde_info_box][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_single_image alignment="center" image="11"][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner padding_size="no-padding" width="2/3"][vc_column_text]
Relax in our friendly cafe with views across the farmyard and fields beyond.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3" offset="vc_hidden-sm vc_hidden-xs"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]

Freshly prepared every day, our food reflects what’s growing in  the farm. In the warm spring or summer weather you can sit out on our lovely terrace with a succulent salad. On chillier days, you can snuggle up near the woodburner with a comforting soup, a fresh coffee, or a luscious slice of pie.

This is a place to linger in, with friends, with books, or in peace with your thoughts. It’s also an excellent source of inspiration on what to do with all those beautiful veggies...

item.title: About Us
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row row_style="full-width" padding_size="no-padding"][vc_column padding_size="no-padding"][wyde_section_separator style="3" background_color="#ffffff" shape_color="#3ab54a"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][wyde_heading style="8" text_align="left" title="We're a family of farmers" subheading="01"][vc_empty_space][vc_column_text]GoGreen Organic Farm is a second-generation organic farm that got its start inthe west hills of Portland, Oregon. the farm was founded by our parents, Martin Gray and Chirs D. Davis, in 1980. We use only organic practices, and we do our best to act as stewards of the land we’re working. The Farm has been certified USDA Organic since 2001.
We grow a wide variety of fruits and vegetables at the farm, with a focus on sustainable production of heritage and specialty varieties. We love to grow food in a way that enriches the soil as well as the people it feeds. We are grateful to be part of an emerging local food economy that includes both amazing growers and a growing army of well-informed passionate eaters.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image alignment="center" image="82"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row background_color="#f5f5f5"][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_single_image alignment="center" image="83"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][wyde_heading style="8" text_align="left" title="Understanding the sometimes harmful methods of modern agriculture, they realized that there was a niche for quality organic produce grown the way that nature intended for it to be-organically."][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row background_color="#614b3d"][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column text_align="center" width="2/3"][vc_single_image alignment="center" image="85"][vc_empty_space height="50px"][vc_custom_heading text="The farm is a USDA certified organic grower by Washington State Department of Agriculture and by Oregon Tilth. We have a total of 150 certified organic acres in vegetable production and 3 acres of certified organic strawberries." font_container="tag:p|font_size:26px|text_align:center|color:%23ffffff|line_height:38px" google_fonts="font_family:Roboto%20Slab%3A100%2C300%2Cregular%2C700|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][wyde_heading style="8" text_align="left" title="Meet The Farmers" subheading="02"][vc_empty_space][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Today, we continue to grow our family on the farm, encouraging strong roots for a better food and agriculture system for all.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space][wyde_team_slider layout="grid"][/vc_column][/vc_row]
